#Text=Football : Robben retires from international football after Netherlands fails to qualify for World Cup
#Text=Friday , October 13 , 2017
#Text=On Tuesday , Dutch football winger and captain Arjen Robben announced retirement from international play after Netherlands failed to qualify for next year 's World Cup in Russia .
#Text=Oranje defeated Sweden 2 – 1 at home , but failed to qualify for a second consecutive major tournament , after last year 's UEFA Euro tournament .
#Text=Robben , playing his 96th international match on Tuesday , made his international debut in April 2003 .

#Text=Netherlands played Sweden at the Amsterdam ArenA in the Dutch capital , and were awarded a penalty kick in the sixteenth minute after a handball from Swedish defender Victor Lindelöf in the penalty area .
#Text=Robben scored from the spot , netting his 36th international goal from a Panenka kick .
#Text=In the 40th minute , Robben scored his second of the night , from outside the box .
#Text=The scoreline remained 2 – 0 at the end of full time .
#Text=Netherlands dominated in ball possession having 69 % .
#Text=The win gave the Oranjes three points , tying with Sweden with nineteen points from all the group stage matches .
#Text=However , Sweden finished second in the Group A table above Netherlands , leading in goals scored .
#Text=In order to play the play-offs for the World Cup , Netherlands needed to defeat Sweden by a seven-goal margin .
#Text=Robben 's second goal brings his tally of international goals to 37 , and is fourth in the list of top scorers for Netherlands , tied with Denis Bergkamp .
#Text=Robben has featured in the FIFA World Cup tournaments of 2006 , 2010 and 2014 .
#Text=He has won a silver medal at the 2010 World Cup , losing to Spain in extra time , and a bronze medal finishing third in 2014 's World Cup in Brazil .
#Text=After the match , Robben said , " I 've been thinking about this for a long time .
